==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pother
<hw>Poth"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>peuteren</ets> to rummage, poke. Cf. <er>Potter</er>,
<er>Pudder</er>.]</ety> <def>Bustle; confusion; tumult; flutter;
bother.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>potter</asp>, and
<asp>pudder</asp>.]</altsp> ⟦ldquo⟧What a <xex>pother</xex> and
stir!⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Oldham.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Coming on with a terrible
<xex>pother</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Wordsworth.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pother</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pother
<hw>Poth"er</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a bustle or stir; to be
fussy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pother</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pother
<hw>Poth"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pothered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pothering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To harass and perplex; to
worry.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pothers</xex> and wearies himself.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

